Here is an example function that you can use to create a shortcode for displaying a list of custom posts:
```php
function custom_post_list_shortcode( $atts ) {
    $atts = shortcode_atts( array(
        'number_of_posts' => 5,
        'category' => '',
        'taxonomy' => '',
    ), $atts, 'custom_post_list' );

    $args = array(
        'post_type' => 'custom_post',
        'posts_per_page' => $atts['number_of_posts'],
    );

    if ( ! empty( $atts['category'] ) ) {
        $args['category_name'] = $atts['category'];
    }

    if ( ! empty( $atts['taxonomy'] ) ) {
        $args['tax_query'] = array(
            array(
                'taxonomy' => $atts['taxonomy'],
                'field'    => 'slug',
                'terms'    => $atts['taxonomy'],
            ),
        );
    }

    $query = new WP_Query( $args );

    if ( $query->have_posts() ) {
        $output = '<ul>';
        while ( $query->have_posts() ) {
            $query->the_post();
            $output .= '<li><a href="' . get_the_permalink() . '">' . get_the_title() . '</a></li>';
        }
        wp_reset_postdata();
        $output .= '</ul>';
    } else {
        $output = 'No custom posts found.';
    }

    return $output;
}
add_shortcode( 'custom_post_list', 'custom_post_list_shortcode' );
```
You can use the shortcode [custom\_post\_list number\_of\_posts="5" category="category-slug" taxonomy="taxonomy-slug"] to display the list of custom post.
You can use it in any post or page and you can change number\_of\_posts, category and taxonomy as per your requirement.

